The paper deals with facial image de-identification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves privacy protection and data security, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a new approach that leverages machine learning techniques such as Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and hyperparameter tuning, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of mixed precision training, which is a technique used to speed up training and reduce memory consumption, and is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves automation of parameter tuning, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
